ChartjsGenj
-----------

This is a quick implementation of a HTML/JavaScript generator for writting
web pages with Chart.js charts. My target was to have something I could
easily generate the charts from Java data, without fighting with strings again
and again and also without external dependencies. Not everything is supported,
and the design can surely be improved, but so far it works for me ;-)

Usage
-----

Distribution zip contains three jar files:

 *  chartjsgenj-x.y.jar (binary)
 *  chartjsgenj-doc-x.y.jar (javadoc)
 *  chartjsgenj-src-x.y.jar (sources

To use the library just add the binary to your project's classpath.
You can use the doc jar to enable autocompletion info in your IDE and
the src jar to access the sources.

Contribute
----------

If you have found some bug and want to send a fix just open an issue
on Github project and submit a pull request:

http://github.com/mones/chartjsgenj

Alternatively you can send a mail to me with the patch.


